<% bot     = Config['irc']['nick'] %>
<% twitter = Config['twitter']['login'] %>

<h2>All available commands for <a href="http://github.com/snusnu/alfred"><%= bot %></a></h2>

<p>
  Alfred can help you collect useful information from irc channels. You can store away posts so that you can use them later
  on when you're writing your project's documentation, wiki pages, blog articles or whatever. You can tag these posts so
  that they are easier to find later on. Of course you're not limited to posting snippets of text. Just post a link to
  <em><%= bot %></em>, say to a <a href="http://pastie.org">pastie</a>, a <a href="http://gist.github.com">gist</a> or some
  interesting blogpost and tag them as you wish. <em><%= bot %></em> has convenient commands to retrieve them later on.
</p>

<h3>Get some info from <%= bot %></h3>

<dl>
  <dt>prints a little info about alfred</dt>
  <dd><em><%= bot %>: identify</em></dd>

  <dt>prints this list of commands</dt>
  <dd><em><%= bot %>: show commands</em></dd>

  <dt>prints a link to all posts</dt>
  <dd><em><%= bot %>: show posts</em></dd>

  <dt>prints a list of available tags</dt>
  <dd><em><%= bot %>: show tags</em></dd>

  <dt>prints a list of available posts tagged with tag</dt>
  <dd><em><%= bot %>: show tag some_tag</em></dd>
</dl>

<h3>Post tagged messages</h3>

<dl>
  <dt>posts a tagged snippet of text to <%= bot %></dt>
  <dd><em><%= bot %>: post[tag1 tag2]: whatever you want to post</em></dd>
</dl>

<h3>Tweet in the name of <em><%= twitter %></em></h3>

<dl>

  <dt>people currently allowed to tweet in the name of <strong><%= twitter %></strong></dt>
  <dd><em><%= Config['allowed'].join(', ') %></em></dd>

  <dt>allow someone to tweet as <strong><%= twitter %></strong> (you must be allowed to do so)</dt>
  <dd><em>/msg <%= bot %> allow irc_nick</em></dd>

  <dt>posts a tagged snippet of text to <%= bot %></dt>
  <dd><em><%= bot %>: post[tag1 tag2]: whatever you want to post</em></dd>

  <dt>send a tweet as <strong><%= twitter %></strong> (you must be allowed to do so)</dt>
  <dd><em><%= bot %>: tweet: the message you want to tweet</em></dd>

  <dt>let <strong><%= twitter %></strong> follow someone on twitter (you must be allowed to do so)</dt>
  <dd><em><%= bot %>: follow twitter_nick</em></dd>
</dl>
